@sipa: If you have a 2880x1800 screen, you barely can't see anything if you don't _scale the UI_. Therefore apple announced the *2 approach. Just double everything, image/icon size, window bars, font, etc. This gives a extremely comfortable result.

Now the problem is, that on Linux, Qt auto-scale the Font and metrics, but leaving out the Icons in Buttons as well as window sizes.
IMO it's just not finished or fixed in all places (QT upstream).
